cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with recognizing human activities in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel deep learning architecture, which involves training end-to-end using Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on two datasets related to sports activities, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
